Concept
A k-vertex colouring of G is an assignment of k colours, $1,2,\cdots,k$ to the vertices of G;
The colouring is proper if no two distince adjacent vertices have the same colour.
chromatic number: \(\chi(G)\), of G is the minimum k for which G is k-colourable;
